Third are the Colombian Andean highland populations (~1400-1500m; see
Niceforo-Maria 1970
), which differ from the holotype in having 184-193 ventrals (versus 180), 127-131 subcaudals (versus 136), and 10-12 infralabials (versus 9). This group likely represents a third species, Synophis cf. bicolor . While we refrain from describing these additional Synophis bicolor -group species here based on limited current sampling, the populations described above likely represent at least two (Ecuadorean Andean highland and Colombian Andean Highland) if not three (E and W Ecuadorean and Colombian Andean highland) species.
